; kreetek.scr 3/31/96

;   Definitions

REGIONDEF 172 DEPART 0
REGIONDEF 172 WELLOFLIFE DISABLED
REGIONDEF 172 TELEPORTATION DISABLED

; Tech Cevent
VARIABLE KREEMINUTE
VARIABLE KREEONCEADAY
VARIABLE SUBCOUNT
VARIABLE SUBADAY
VARIABLE SUBWHERE
VARIABLE SUBMOVE
VARIABLE KREERECORD
VARIABLE TECHCOUNT
; Tech Hall
VARIABLE KREETELEV
VARIABLE KREECOMPUTI
VARIABLE KREEENDIE
VARIABLE KREEBUT
VARIABLE SUBLADDER
VARIABLE KREELOOKTECH
VARIABLE SCIEN
; Subway
VARIABLE SUBWAYCOINS
VARIABLE TOKENIN
VARIABLE GRATEOPEN
VARIABLE KREEWALL
VARIABLE STDOOR ; For Tunnel door
;
MACRO 9
;
IFTOUCH 1
  IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
      IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
        DAMAGEPLR ELECTRIC 300 15,000 watts of high voltage energy grounds itself through you!
        ECHO OTHERS You see a strobe-light affect as %n is thrown back from the rail!
        POSITION LAY
      ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFENTRY -1
	IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
		IFVAR PLRSINROOM > MONINROOM
			RANDOM DUMMY1 1 100 0
			IFVAR DUMMY1 > 85
				GENMON 147
				ECHO ALL A subway rat runs in.
			ENDIF
		ENDIF
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB DIG -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You can't dig through solid concrete!
ENDIF
;
MACRO 10

;			**** Tech Guild   *****

NUMBER 350
NAME Tech. Hall, training room
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This room is filled with mats and sparring equipment to handle all forms
of combat. In one corner sits many targets for both combat and mind
attacks. In the opposite corner sits a strange machine with a few crystal
dials and screens. Hanging on one wall is a giant plaque fashioned from
long dead circuit boards. The lettering on the plaque reads: "Magic is the
Disease, Technology is the Cure." Under the plaque, sits an shiny metal
door. On the opposite wall is a familiar looking device. A computer
terminal rests in the corner.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 1493 ; Changed from 351 so Lawkeepers Interogation room could be 351
; which would allow them to ARREST people in there.
ITEM 0 943 ADJ1=288 ADJ2=192 VAL1=5000 VAL2=1001 VAL3=777 CLOSED LOCKED
ITEM 1 882            ; power machine
ITEM 2 397            ; hand scanning device
ITEM 3 72 VAL2=349    ; opening for elevator
ITEM 4 1480           ; Thermite's shell
ITEM 5 901            ; computer
ITEM 6 422 ADJ1=259   ; SWITCH

EXTEND 4 of a familiar looking mechanoid

; call 56

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
You see a large combination of refined metal and other unknown substances
that make up this large technological wonder. A giant red switch rests in
plain view.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
You see a strange device attached to the wall with a flat smooth surface
and what appears to be an outline of a hand.
*DESCRIPTION_END

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 4
The former housing of Thermite Eveready, one of the first Mechanoids. He
chose to forego his Mechanoid life to return to what he once was.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFVERB FLIP 6
  IFVAR PVAL51 = 0
       EQUAL PVAL51 1
       ECHO PLAYER Suddenly the machine begins to glow.
       PLREVENT 2
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO ALL You hear a voice from a speaker say, "Power level now at 100 percent."
   ELSE
     EQUAL PVAL51 0
     PLREVENT 2
     CONTPLREVENT
     ECHO ALL %cThe machine slowy rumbles to a halt as the power is cut.
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFENTRY
 IFVAR ORG = 7
  IFVAR INTNUM68 = 0
    ECHO PLAYER %cWalking through this hall, you become eager to begin your pursuits of technology.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER %cPerhaps you can recall something about the equipment in this room...
    GMMSG ** %n has been given the hint about TECH ratings.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB RECALL 5
 IFVAR ORG = 7
  IFVAR SKILL32 > 1
    CLEARVERB
    GMMSG **  %n has remembered the computer command.
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou seem to recall remembering something about a computer command...
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER ...what was it...
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER         ...Oh yeah. "Computer, Identify."
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou seem to recall remembering something about a computer command...
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER ..however, you seem to lack the ability to recall it.
  ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 5
  IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You see a terminal for a central computer. A small screen a
    ECHO PLAYER multi-directional micro-phone and a speaker make up its
    ECHO PLAYER main components. Resting next to it, a pretty large piece
    ECHO PLAYER of equipment, with the letters "STORAGE" stenciled across
    ECHO PLAYER the front.
    ECHO PLAYER %cIt glows as power flows through it's circuitry.
    CLEARVERB
  ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER You see a terminal for a central computer. A small screen a
    ECHO PLAYER multi-directional micro-phone and a speaker make up its
    ECHO PLAYER main components. Resting next to it, a pretty large piece
    ECHO PLAYER of equipment, with the letters "STORAGE" stenciled across
    ECHO PLAYER the front.
    ECHO PLAYER %cIt's screen is dim, devoid of power.
    CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFTOUCH 1
 IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The machine seems to hum now, more than vibrate.
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 1
   IFITEM 1 OPEN
      IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You glance inside the massive machine and see a brightly glowing power cell inerconnected with several components.
         ECHO PLAYER The light seems to nearly blind you as you try to stare directly at the odd looking cell
       ELSE
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You glance inside the massive machine only to see a maze of interconnected wires and cirtcuits.
         ECHO PLAYER A platinum colored power cell, although connected, is dark.
       ENDIF
     ELSE
   ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB TOUCH 2
  IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
  IFVAR PVAL56 = 0
    IFVAR ORG = 7
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
        EQUAL FLAG1 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You place your hand on the device, and it glows for a moment.
        ECHO OTHERS %n places %h hand on the device and it glows for a moment.
        IFVAR INTNUM3 = 167
          IFVAR GEN = 0
          	ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity confirmed, Cyber-GuildMaster %n."
          ENDIF
          IFVAR GEN = 1
          	ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity confirmed, Cyber-GuildMistress %n."
          ENDIF
          IFVAR GEN = 2
          	ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity confirmed, Cyber-Guild-It %n."
          ENDIF
        ENDIF
        IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 167
	        IFVAR ORGRANK < 50
	          ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity confirmed, Cyber-Punk %n."
	        ENDIF
	        IFVAR ORGRANK > 49
	          IFVAR ORGRANK < 100
	            ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity confirmed, Cyber-Neer %n."
	          ENDIF
	        ENDIF
	        IFVAR ORGRANK > 99
	          IFVAR ORGRANK < 200
	            ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity confirmed, Cyber-Hero %n."
	          ENDIF
	        ENDIF
	        IFVAR ORGRANK > 199
	          ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity confirmed, Cyber-Master %n."
	        ENDIF
        ENDIF
            IFVAR INTNUM68 = 0
              RANDOM INTNUM68 1 21 0
              STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 randomly set to %0.
            ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 5
                ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are ignorant of technology."
                STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	            GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- ignorant
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 10
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 4
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a novice with technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- novice
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 20
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 9
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a student of technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- student
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 30
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 19
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a technician of technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- technician
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 40
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 29
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a scholar of technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- scholar
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 50
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 39
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a professor of technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- professor
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 60
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 49
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a doctor of technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- doctor
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 70
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 59
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a engineer of technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- engineer
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 < 80
                IFVAR INTNUM68 > 69
                  ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are an advanced engineer of technology."
                  STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	              GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- advanced engineer
                ENDIF
              ENDIF
              IFVAR INTNUM68 > 79
                ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "%n, you are a wiz kid of technology."
                STRCVT 0 INTNUM68
	            GMMSG ** %n's INTNUM 68 = %0. -- whiz kid
              ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You place your hand on the device, and it glows for a moment.
      ECHO OTHERS %n places %h hand on the device and it glows for a moment.
      ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Identity unknown."
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB TOUCH 2
  IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
      IFVAR ORG = 7
        IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
          IFVAR KREETELEV = 1
            EQUAL KREETELEV 0
            ECHO ALL A section of the wall, next to the strange device, slides apart, exposing an opening.
            NEWITEM 3 72 VAL2=349
            AFFECT 348
            ECHO ALL An opening disappears, to be replaced by a seamless metal wall.
            REMOVEITEM 3
            AFFECT 349
            ECHO ALL You feel a slight descending sensation and then an opening slides apart.
            SETITEMVAL 2 2 350
            AFFECT 350
          ENDIF
        ENDIF
      ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER %cYou feel a slight electric tingle run through you, but nothing else happens.
      ENDIF
  ELSE
   ECHO PLAYER %cNothing happens. There is no power.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY COMPUTER,_IDENTIFY.
  IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
      IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
        EQUAL FLAG1 1
        ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "Please place your hand on the scanning device for verification of identification."
      ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY COMPUTER,_MY_TECH_RATING.
	IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
		ECHO ALL %cThe computer intones, "This command has been deleted. Please use the "Identify" command."
	ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB OPEN 1
 IFITEM 1 OPEN
   CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER The access panel has already been opened.
 ELSE
   IFVAR INTNUM68 > 4
       CLEARVERB
       OPEN 1
       ECHO PLAYER You look the machine over and find an access panel.
       PLREVENT 1
       CONTPLREVENT
       ECHO PLAYER You open it and put it aside.
       ECHO OTHERS %n removes the access panel and sets it aside.
   ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You lack the expertise to open up this complex piece of machinery...
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER ...but, you think you got it figured out, now.
    ADD INTNUM68 1
    ECHO PLAYER %cYou feel you have gained technological insight.
   ENDIF
 ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLOSE 1
  IFITEM 1 OPEN
    IFVAR INTNUM68 > 4
      CLEARVERB
      CLOSE 1
      ECHO PLAYER You pick up the access panel and replace it.
      ECHO OTHERS %n takes the access panel and closes up the compartment.
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER You lack the expertise to close up this complex piece of machinery.
      CLEARVERB
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The machine's access panel is closed.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB2 PUT 1
   IFITEM 1 OPEN
       IFVAR ARCHNUM = 844
          CLEARVERB
          ECHO PLAYER There is no room for that.
        ENDIF
    ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB READ 1
  IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
     ECHO PLAYER You glance at the power dial and see that the power level is at 100 percent.
     ECHO OTHERS %n takes a reading off one of the dials.
     CLEARVERB
  ELSE
     ECHO PLAYER You glance at the power dial and see that the machine is off.
     ECHO OTHERS %n takes a reading off one of the dials.
     CLEARVERB
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB RECALL 1
      IFVAR INTNUM68 < 5
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You analyze the unit...
        ECHO OTHERS %n studies the %a.
        PLREVENT 2
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO PLAYER So far, you lack the technological training to be able to identify this machine...
        PLREVENT 1
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO PLAYER ..but it doesn't look unfamiliar to you.
        ADD INTNUM68 1
        ECHO PLAYER %cYou feel you have gained technological insight.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR INTNUM68 > 4
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You analyze the unit...
        ECHO OTHERS %n studies the %a.
        PLREVENT 2
        CONTPLREVENT
        ECHO PLAYER You recogonize this to be the machinery that Renegor found when the the guild was renovated. You notice that despite its apparent age, that it is in pristine condition.
        IFVAR INTNUM68 > 9
          PLREVENT 2
          CONTPLREVENT
          ECHO PLAYER %cYou further recogonize this machine as a chemical-to-mechanical energy transformer.
          IFVAR INTNUM68 > 14
            PLREVENT 2
            CONTPLREVENT
            ECHO PLAYER %cSupplied with chemical power from a cell, this machine could provide incredible levels of mechanical energy for extended durations of time.
            ECHO PLAYER The machine seems to be running more efficiently now.
          ENDIF
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
ENDIF

ORGDEF 7 invite guild 350 Technologists_Guild

TRAINING 1 10
TRAINING 3 43
TRAINING 5 15
TRAINING 6 51
TRAINING 8 15
TRAINING 9 49
TRAINING 10 25
TRAINING 11 25
TRAINING 12 10
TRAINING 13 25
TRAINING 20 15
TRAINING 22 17
TRAINING 25 15
TRAINING 26 76
TRAINING 27 30
TRAINING 28 30
TRAINING 32 11

NUMBER 348
NAME Technologists Hall, foyer
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
The foyer of the Technologists Hall features many ancient and intricate
murals depicting scenes of the incredible technology of ancient times.
Replicas and blueprints of technological items are on display elsewhere on
the walls. Volumes of research books and notes can be seen in bookshelves
and on the far wall hangs and enormous plaque, which reads: "The Future,
through the Technology of the Past." A vacant desk with a book on it sits
in one corner. Underneath the huge plaque, attached to the wall is a
strange looking device. A titanium door leads back outside.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 200 ADJ1=328 VAL2=261
ITEM 1 423 ADJ1=641
ITEM 2 397                      ; device

IFENTRY -1
 IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
     IFVAR KREETELEV = 1
        AFFECT 349
        IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 0
          AFFECT 348
          REMOVEITEM 3
          EQUAL KREETELEV 0
          ECHO ALL The opening in the wall disappears to be replaced by a seamless wall.
          AFFECT 349
          ECHO ALL The opening disappears and you feel a slight descending sensation before the opening re-appears.
          SETITEMVAL 2 2 350
          AFFECT 348
          AFFECT 350
          ECHO ALL A section of the wall by the strange device slides apart, exposing an opening.
          NEWITEM 3 72 VAL2=349
          AFFECT 348
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB TOUCH 1
 IFVAR PVAL51 = 1
 IFVAR ORG ! 7
 IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
  EQUAL FLAG1 1
  ECHO ALL A computerized voice intones, "The Technologists on this plane are being alerted to your interest."
  AFFECT 590
  ECHO ALL ** Kree, %n just fondled the Techno-book.
  AFFECT 348
  IFSEEK 900
