        ECHO PLAYER of transportation capable of moving many people to and from preset
        ECHO PLAYER destinations in a timely and cost efficient manner. Tunnels inter-
        ECHO PLAYER connected under the city and were used by long cylnderical electric
        ECHO PLAYER powered vehicles guided along a rail system.
      ELSE
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER %cYou remember being told about giant snake-like machines that would
        ECHO PLAYER move through tunnels in the ground.
      ENDIF
    ELSE
      IFVAR INTNUM68 > 4
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER %cThe turnstile was an affective means of controling the flow
        ECHO PLAYER through the station as it forced everyone to pay and prevented
        ECHO PLAYER the inevitable pushing wars when conditions became too crowded.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    IFVAR INTNUM68 > 4
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER %cThe token machine, as it was called, because it dispensed tokens
      ECHO PLAYER in exchange for the local currency, was as much a permanent fixture
      ECHO PLAYER in this setting as the commuters who used them.
      IFVAR INTNUM68 > 9
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER %cIt dawns on you as you examine what is left of the etchings
        ECHO PLAYER on the machine's shell that the currency used long ago to
        ECHO PLAYER make this machine dispense tokens was not unlike today's
        ECHO PLAYER minted currency. The rounded shapes, could possibly be
        ECHO PLAYER matched with combinations of current coins and fool
        ECHO PLAYER the machine into giving up a token.
        IFVAR INTNUM68 > 19
          CLEARVERB
          PLREVENT 1
          CONTPLREVENT
          ECHO PLAYER %cYou mull it over in your head and deduce that if you PAY 10
          ECHO PLAYER gold coins, that should appease the machines's internal checks.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

