NUMBER 3713
NAME Subway, Hidden Room
REGION 172
ASTRAL
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You step into a rather large room for a steam tunnel. As far as you can tell,
this room is out of place. Steam pipes criss-cross the room, but they do not look
as used, nor are they dripping with moisture. The room looks as if it had been
lived in at some point in time, though from the looks of the place, not since the
Cataclysm. A small, decayed cot rests in one corner. The wall is covered with
yellowed and near illegible paper. A metal desk sits across from the cot. On the
far wall, the steam pipes seem all intersect in some kind of machine imbedded
into the wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 420 ; wall
ITEM 2 853 ; machine
ITEM 3 1189
ITEM 8 201 ADJ1=192 ; desk
ITEM 5 436 ADJ1=88 ; cot
ITEM 6 365 ADJ1=265 ADJ2=408 ; platform
ITEM 7 247 ADJ1=259

EXTEND 2 completely integrated with the steam pipes and the wall
EXTEND 7 on top of the desk

IFPREVERB LOOK 3
	IFVAR PER > 100
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You can see the outline of a doorway cut through some of the pipes
		ECHO PLAYER and the wall beyond. No wonder those pipes were empty and unuesed!
	ELSE
		ECHO PLAYER You don't notice anything out of the ordinary.
		CLEARVERB
	ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 8
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER The desk is completely stripped of anything useful. The moisture of the room seems to have corroded or decayed almost everything. In the far corner of the desk, long since rust-fused with the desk is what looks to be a sound recording device. By the looks of it, only one button looks like it might work.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 7
	CLEARVERB
	EQUAL ROUNDTIME 30
	ECHO OTHERS %n pushes the red button on the desk.
	ECHO PLAYER You push the red button on the desk.
	ECHO ALL %cSound comes from a rusted pile of metal that once must have been a functioning speaker. Now, you can barely recognize the sound as understandable language.
	PLREVENT 2
	CONTPLREVENT
	ECHO ALL Then the sound begins to clear up and the words become understandable: "Cursed! Cursed I am! Damn me! I could not live without her and now,
	PLREVENT 3
	CONTPLREVENT
	ECHO ALL even death is too good for me! Aaieieieieieieie!"
	PLREVENT 3
	CONTPLREVENT
	ECHO ALL %cThe last sound you can hear is a loud SNAP, as if a tree suddenly cracked under a tremendous weight.
ENDIF
			
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You look over the wall carefully. There are many scraps of paper hanging from it. Most of them are yellow, crumbling and illegible. One, however, still has some print on it:
	ECHO PLAYER %c          Scient...Insa...Commi tt d...
	ECHO PLAYER           .........Disapp................
	ECHO PLAYER           ....sumed dea..................
	ECHO PLAYER %cThe remainder of the words are not legible.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 6
	CLEARVERB
	ECHO PLAYER You can see a pentagram painted on the round platform with dried blood.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PULL 3
	IFVAR STDOOR = 0
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You pull on the cooler pipes and the wall opens revealing a doorway!
		ECHO OTHERS %n pulls on some of the unused pipes and opens the wall to reveal a doorway!
		NEWITEM 4 1341 VAL2=782
		AFFECT 782
		ECHO ALL You see a section of the wall swing in revealing a doorway!
		NEWITEM 4 1341 VAL2=3713
		AFFECT 3713
		EQUAL STDOOR 1
	ELSE
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER The wall has already been swung open, revealing a doorway.
	ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB PUSH 3
	IFVAR STDOOR = 1
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You pushes the wall closed, sealing up the doorway once again.
		ECHO OTHERS %n pushes the wall closed, sealing up the doorway once again.
		REMOVEITEM 4
		AFFECT 782
		REMOVEITEM 4
		ECHO ALL You see the open section of the wall swing close.
		AFFECT 3713
		EQUAL STDOOR 0
	ELSE
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER The wall won't budge.
	ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB LOOK 2
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You can see the outline of a machine imbedded into the wall itself. Steam pipes seem to inter-connect with all parts of of it. A small platform protrudes from the wall.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB RECALL 2
	IFVAR INTNUM68 > 20
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You quickly try to determine the machine's function by examing it's components. The best you can come up with is a device that focuses energy via the steam pipes. The platform seems to be the the center piece, but you are not sure of what.
		ECHO PLAYER %cYou can see no controls of any kind anywhere.
	ELSE
		CLEARVERB
		ECHO PLAYER You quickly try to determine the machine's function by examing it's components. The best you can come up with is a device that uses alot of steam, hence all of the steam pipes converging on it.
	ENDIF
ENDIF

IFVERB SMELL -1
	ECHO PLAYER %cYou smell dank mildew everywhere.
ENDIF

